text:
Docstrings are considered as such by python only if they are the first
statement in the file/block.  Even if they are preceded by a
`from __future__` import they are interpreted as just a string.
title: Move docstrings above `from __future__` imports.

Pull request merge from x746e/oauthlib:moved-docstrings-to-the-top to idan/oauthlib:master

text: Style fixes are always welcome. Thanks :)
Actually it's not (only) about styling: the problem was that before this change docstrings were not placed into `module.__doc__` (and that's why I spotted this).

Move docstrings above `from __future__` imports.

Docstrings are considered as such by python only if they are the first
statement in the file/block.  Even if they are preceded by a
`from __future__` import they are interpreted as just a string.
